Folk music:
\b0 \
\pard\ri0

\fs20 \cf0 	Folk music is music that is played or sung by ordinary people (not professional musicians). It is traditional music that people learn by listening to other people playing it and then copying them. We say that the tradition is \'93orally transmitted\'94 or \'93handed down orally\'94, meaning that the music is not written down but taught by speaking (\'93oral\'94 means \'93belonging to the mouth\'94). Every country has its own traditional music. Folk song is part of folk music. ( And, a folksinger is a person who can sing folk songs.) \
	Folk music is music for everybody to play and listen to; it is participatory. In this way it is different from classical music which is mainly developed by professional musicians for a smaller group of people. Folk music is part of a popular culture. In many parts of the world nearly all music is folk music. In the 1960s a new type of music was started by Bob Dylan who mixed traditional folk song with rock and roll. This music is sometimes also called \'93folk\'94.\
